title: song_of_third_period_(vocaloid)
body:
The 12th song in the Clockwork Lullaby series, set concurrently to [[master of the heavenly yard (vocaloid)|]]. It's a group song, sung by [[Hatsune Miku]], [[KAITO (vocaloid)|]], [[MEIKO (vocaloid)|]], [[Kagamine Rin]], [[Kagamine Len]], [[Megurine Luka]], [[Kamui Gakupo]], [[GUMI]], and [[Yowane Haku]].

Based on asset #23793480, the characters singing include [[Michaela (evillious nendaiki)|]], [[Arte (evillious nendaiki)|]], [[Lukana Octo]], [[Miroku Mei]], [[Clarith]], [[Inukichi (enbizaka no shitateya)|]], [[Germaine Avadonia]], [[Gumillia]], [[Mikulia Greeonio]], [[Hel Jakko]], [[Anne Lucifen d'Autriche]], [[Kyle Marlon]], [[Pollo (evillious nendaiki)|]], and [[Nyoze Octo]].

title: chinese_text
body:
The image contains text in any form of Chinese. Usually, this means Mandarin Chinese.

There are two systems in writing Chinese, [[traditional chinese text|Traditional]] and [[simplified chinese text|Simplified]] (e.g. 馬 vs. 马). Mainland China, Singapore, and Malaysia use Simplified Chinese while Hong Kong, Macau, and Taiwan use Traditional Chinese. There is also an official system for romanizing Chinese known as [[pinyin text|Hanyu Pinyin]]. 

h4. See also

* [[bopomofo text]]
* [[cantonese text]]
* [[minnan text]]
* [[oracle bone script]]
* [[pinyin text]]
* [[sichuanese text]]
* [[seal script]]
* [[Tag group:Text]]

body:
A fictional character from the [[Gundam]] universe. He appears in [[Zeta Gundam]] and [[Gundam ZZ]].

title: sari
body:
A simple feminine garment made of a length of unstitched samite. It is worn around the waist just below the navel, tucked and pleated, wrapping around the body twice, the remaining length folded and draped over the shoulder.  It can also be raised to drape over the head for modesty and to conceal ones features.

title: renault_ft
body:
The Renault FT, also referred to as FT-17 and FT17, was a French light [[tank]] that was among the most revolutionary and influential tank designs in history. The FT was the first production tank to have its armament within a fully rotating turret. The Renault FT's configuration – crew compartment at the front, engine compartment at the back, and main armament in a revolving turret – became and remains the standard tank layout.

h4. See also

title: washboard
body:
A washboard is a tool designed for hand washing clothing. The use of washboards have fallen out of use in the developed world, where [[washing_machine|washing machines]] have become common. For the developing world, washboards may still be a common sight. In some parts of the United States washboards are used as a musical instrument.

A washboard works by rubbing wet clothing against its corrugated or ridged side.  This helps to remove dirt from the clothing through abrasion.  If soap is used, the rubbing action helps to drive soap through the clothing and allows the soap to carry dirt away.

title: ole_tower
body:
[b]Over Legend Endless Tower[/b] (Abbreviated as [i]Ole Tower[/i]) is a Japanese webgame developed by SE Mobile and Online Co.Ltd.

The main purpose of the game is to build an "endless" tower using different "tool girls" (Kenhime) at your disposal. The game also includes a combat system in a phase-by-phase and turn-based fashion, similar to many other games on DMM including [[Kantai Collection]].

The game has gained popularity with a moderate amount of [[Kantai Collection]] fans due to the obvious similarity.

title: logan_(movie)
body: Logan is a 2017 American superhero film starring [[Hugh Jackman]] as the titular character. It is the tenth film in the [[X-Men film series]] and the third and final installment in the Wolverine trilogy, following [[X-Men Origins: Wolverine]] (2009) and [[The Wolverine]] (2013). The film, which takes inspiration from the "Old Man Logan" comics storyline by Mark Millar and Steve McNiven, follows an aged [[Wolverine (x-men)|]] and an extremely ill [[Charles Xavier]] who must defend a young mutant named [[x-23|Laura]] from the Reavers led by [[Donald Pierce]] and Zander Rice.

body:
The H35 was a French light [[tank]] developed prior to [[World War II]]. Despite having been designed from 1933 as a rather slow but well-armoured light infantry support tank, the type was initially rejected by the French Infantry because it proved difficult to steer while driving cross-country, and was instead adopted in 1936 by the French Cavalry.

title: somua_s35
body:
The S35 was a French Cavalry [[tank]] of [[World War II]]. Built from 1936 until 1940 to equip the armoured divisions of the Cavalry, it was for its time a relatively agile medium-weight tank, superior in armour and armament to its French and foreign competitors, such as the contemporary versions of the German [[Panzer III]]. It was constructed from well-sloped, mainly cast, armour sections, that however made it expensive to produce and time-consuming to maintain.

h4. See also

* [[List of Ground Vehicles]]
* "External Link - Wikipedia: S35":http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/SOMUA_S35

title: marder_iii
body:
The [b]Marder III[/b] is the name for a type of [[World War II]] German [[self-propelled artillery]] used as [[tank]] destroyers and built on the chassis of a [[Panzer 38(t)]] tank. 

The German word [i]Marder[/i] means "marten" in English. They were in production from 1942 to 1944 and served with the [[Wehrmacht]] on all fronts until the end of the war.

h4. External links

* "Wikipedia: Marder III":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Marder_III

title: panzer_38(t)
body:
Originally a Czech tank of pre-World War II design. After Czechoslovakia was taken over by Germany, it was adopted by the German Army, seeing service in the invasions of Poland, France and Russia. Production ended in 1942, when its armament was deemed inadequate. In all, over 1400 were manufactured. The chassis continued to be produced for [[Marder III]] (1942-1944) and [[jagdpanzer_38(t)|Hetzer]] (1944-1945) tank destroyers, turretless assault guns, anti-tank guns and anti-aircraft guns.

The (t) stands for [i]tschechisch[/i], the German word for Czech; the Czechoslovak military designation was LT vz. 38. Manufacturer's designations included TNH series, TNHPS, LTP and LTH). The special vehicle designation for the tank in Germany was Sd.Kfz. 140.

h4. See also

* [[List of Ground Vehicles]]
* [[Girls und Panzer]]

h4. External links

title: waifu2x
body:
[i]Single-Image Super-Resolution for Anime-Style Art using Deep Convolutional Neural Networks.[/i]

An [[upscaled|upscaling]] and [[noise reduction]] algorithm specifically designed to work on 2D anime-style art.

Like any other form of [[third-party edit|third-party]] [[upscaled|upscaling]], third-party Waifu2X upscales are only accepted if the original version is not available, and should be flagged/deleted if the original picture is uploaded.

If you want to upload a picture that has gone through Waifu2X, follow [[help:image source]] for instructions on how to try and find the original picture first, and only upload the upscaled version if reverse searching fails.

h4. See also

* [[image sample]]
* [[resized]]

h4. External links

* Online demo application: https://www.waifu2x.net/

body:
A character from [[GALZOO Island]], who serves as [[Leopold Maala]]'s arch-rival and adoptive sister. 

Throughout the game, she will attempt to capture and tame any Gal Monsters not captured by Leopold, and will succeed in doing so if Leopold takes too long. To illustrate this, she is always guaranteed to capture and tame a [[Tenten (Alicesoft)|]], who becomes her accomplace.

Additionally, Erina also makes a cameo in [[Sengoku Rance]], serving as a bonus unit after completing the game once.

title: amiya_aranha_(2nd_costume)
body:

This appearance is an [[emo fashion]]-styled look consisting of a [[torn shirt|torn]] [[black shirt|black]] [[print shirt]], a [[black skirt|black]] [[see-through skirt]], and [[black footwear|black]] [[platform footwear]] with [[torn socks|torn]] [[black socks|black]] [[fishnet socks]]. Her accessories include a [[detached collar]], [[striped sleeves|striped]] [[detached sleeves]] worn [[sleeves past wrists|past her wrists]], [[bandaged leg|bandages on her left leg]] and a single [[o-ring thigh strap]] connected to a [[garter straps|garter strap]].

For her [[official alternate hairstyle|hairstyle]] in this costume, it features [[multiple hairpins]] and a [[black bow|black]] [[hair bow]] pinning her bangs to the side and exposing her [[forehead]], revealing that she has a hidden [[extra eyes|second set of eyes]], which have [[black sclera]]. She also wears [[nail polish]] in the appearance, with [[black nails|black fingernails]] and [[toenail polish|toenails]].

title: saesee_tiin
body: Character from [[Star Wars]], Saesee Tiin, a Force-sensitive Iktotchi male from the moon Iktotch, was a [[Jedi]] Master who served on the Jedi High Council during the last years of the Galactic Republic. A skilled lightsaber combatant and starfighter pilot, Tiin fought in the Clone Wars as a Jedi General of the Grand Army of the Republic. He and Agen Kolar were slain by Darth Sidious and became the first victims of the Great Jedi Purge shortly before fellow Jedi Master Kit Fisto when a team of High Council members, organized by [[Mace Windu]] who was betrayed by [[Anakin Skywalker]] shortly before Darth Sidious killed Windu as well, confronted the Sith Lord, who was revealed to be the true identity of Supreme Chancellor Palpatine, who would proceed to destroy the Jedi Order.

title: kit_fisto
body: Character from [[Star Wars]], Kit Fisto was a Force-sensitive Nautolan male [[Jedi]] Master during the final years of the Galactic Republic. Fisto was known as an expert swordsman, possessing some of the finest dueling skills in the Jedi Order. A celebrated fighter, Fisto served as a Jedi General of the Grand Army of the Republic during the Clone Wars, a galaxy-wide conflict between the Republic and Confederacy of Independent Systems. He fought in various campaigns and over the course of the war, was accepted as a member of the Jedi High Council.

title: iceman_(x-men)
body: Iceman (Robert Louis "Bobby" Drake) is a superhero appearing in American comic books published by [[marvel|Marvel Comics]] and is a founding member of the [[X-Men]]. Created by writer Stan Lee and artist/co-plotter Jack Kirby, the character first appeared in The X-Men #1 (Sept. 1963). Iceman is a mutant born with superhuman abilities. He has the ability to manipulate ice and cold by freezing water vapor around him. This allows him to freeze objects, as well as cover his body with ice.

title: alien_(1979)
body:
[quote][i]In space, no one can hear you scream...[/i] - Main tagline.[/quote]

[b]Alien[/b] is a 1979 [[science fiction]] [[horror (theme)|]] film. It is directed by Ridley Scott and stars Tom Skerritt, Sigourney Weaver, Veronica Cartwright, Harry Dean Stanton, John Hurt, Ian Holm and Yaphet Kotto. The film is the first of the [[Alien (series)|]] franchise.

The film's title refers to its primary antagonist: a highly lethal [[alien]] monster that attacks the crew of a [[spacecraft]].

Dan O'Bannon wrote the screenplay from a story by him and Ronald Shusett, drawing influence from previous works of science fiction and horror. The film was produced through Brandywine Productions and distributed by 20th Century Fox, with producers David Giler and Walter Hill making significant revisions and additions to the script. The titular [[xenomorph|Alien]] and its accompanying elements were designed by Swiss surrealist artist [[H.R. Giger]], while concept artists Moebius, Ron Cobb and Chris Foss designed the human aspects of the film.

h4. Humans

title: anmitsu_(dessert)
body:
A popular Japanese [[dessert]] consisting of small [[jelly cube|cubes]] of [[agar]] jelly dissolved with [[water]] or [[fruit]] [[juice]]. It is served in a [[bowl]] with sweet azuki bean paste or anko (the [i]an[/i] part of [i]anmitsu[/i]), boiled peas, and a variety of fruits such as [[peach]] slices, mikan, pieces of [[pineapple]]s, and [[cherry|cherries]]. The anmitsu usually comes with a small pot of sweet black syrup, or mitsu (the [i]mitsu[/i] part of [i]anmitsu[/i]) which one pours onto the jelly before eating.

h4.See also

* [[Mitsumame]]
* [[Tag Group:Food Tags]]

title: unebi_(cruiser)
body:
A Japanese protected cruiser built in France. Launched in late 1886, it mysteriously disappeared on its maiden voyage to Japan with the loss of all hands aboard the ship. Because of the ship's disappearance, the Japanese never worked with French shipyards again and instead entrusted itself to British shipyards.

title: hiryuu_(azur_lane)
body:
[[Azur Lane]]'s personification of the Japanese aircraft carrier [i]Hiryuu[/i], voiced by [[Ishigami Shizuka]].

h4. Appearance
In both base and retrofit forms, she has [[long hair|long]] [[white hair]], [[rabbit ears]], and [[blue eyes]]. Her [[flight deck]] is attached to one side while she launches her planes as [[hanafuda]] cards.

In her base form, she wears blue-colored [[Japanese clothes]] mixed with a modern [[blue skirt]] and a red belt with an anchor attached. She also wears regular white [[socks]], heeled shoes, and a [[single glove|single]] [[black gloves|black glove]] on her right hand.

For her retrofit form, see her [[Hiryuu (retrofit) (azur lane)|corresponding page.]]


h4. History
In real life, she was conceived as an improved [[Souryuu (Azur Lane)|]] design to correct the seakeeping issues of the latter. Her island was located on the port side, one of the only two carriers in history (alongside [[Akagi (Azur Lane)|]]) with that configuration.

Her aviators were primarily responsible for the sinking of [[Arizona (Azur Lane)|]] in Pearl Harbor.

In the [[battle of Midway]], she was the only one out of four spared the onslaught of the American dive bombers in the morning strike, trailing them on the way to the US carriers, where her aviators crippled [[Yorktown (Azur Lane)|]]. A later afternoon strike finally put her out of action, and she was later scuttled with her Carrier Division commander [[Yamaguchi Tamon]] choosing to go down with her (although references to Tamon-maru are almost none in her Azur Lane incarnation).

title: hatakaze_(azur_lane)
body:
The personification of the [i]Kamikaze[/i]-class destroyer [i]Hatakaze[/i] in [[Azur Lane]], first released in the Crimson Echoes event of January 2019.

In-game, she is shown bespectacled, having [[long hair|long]] [[black hair]] tied into [[twintails]] and possessing [[animal ears]]. She also wears traditional [[Japanese clothes]] ([[kimono]] top and [[yellow skirt]]) and [[black socks|black]] printed [[kneehighs]]. She is also shown holding an [[omamori]].
Her rig contains two 12 cm single mounts and two 53.3 cm twin torpedo tubes, one gun and torpedo mount per side.

Historically, her advanced age meant that like her other sisters, she was relegated to escort duties, only seeing frontline action in the battle of the Sunda Strait in early 1942.
She was sunk by aircraft from [[Ticonderoga (Azur Lane)|]] and other US carriers in Kaohsiung after escorting one of these convoys in January 1945.

title: flower_tact
body:
In [[Heartcatch Precure!]], they are the wands used by the Pretty Cures to purify the Desertrian monsters of the week. The Tacts are individually named after their owners, but together are called Flower Tacts. Only [[Cure Sunshine]] doesn't have a Flower Tact - she uses the [[Shiny Tambourine (heartcatch Precure!)|]] instead.

* [[Cure Blossom]] uses the Blossom Tact for Pink Forte Wave, Floral Power Fortissimo (with Marine) and Shining Fortissimo (with Marine and Sunshine)

* [[Cure Marine]] uses the Marine Tact for Blue Forte Wave, Floral Power Fortissino (with Blossom) and Shining Fortissimo (with Blossom and Sunshine)

* [[Cure Moonlight]] uses the Moon Tact for Silver Forte Wave and a solo version of Floral Power Fortissimo

* [[Dark Precure]] uses the Dark Tact for Dark Forte Wave and Dark Power Fortissimo

title: hammann_(azur_lane)
body:
[[Azur Lane]]'s personification of the destroyer [i]Hammann[/i], most famous for sinking alongside [i]Yorktown[/i] during the Battle of Midway.

She is a [[white_hair|white-haired]] girl with [[blue eyes]] and an [i]extremely[/i] [[tsundere]] personality, constantly referring to the [[Commander  (azur lane)|]] as a pervert. She is also highly protective of [[Yorktown (azur_lane)|]] and sometimes finds herself subject to pranks launched by her sister. Curiously for an American destroyer in the game, she is dressed as a [[maid]] and her retrofit further emphasizes this, though she bears no apparent relation to the Royal Maids such as [[Belfast (azur_lane)|]] or [[Sirius (azur_lane)|]]. Furthermore, while her [[cat ears]] bear resemblance to ships belonging to the Sakura Empire, they are [[fake animal ears]] in a [[headband]].

body:
Magia Baiser's La Verita transformation she unlocked during her battle with [[Tada Randa]]. Her horns go from sprouting from the sides of her head to coming out of her forehead, and change color from white to a dark color. In addition, they go from looking like typical demon horns to looking like spider legs. Her costume is replaced with a cut-apart leotard with coattails and other embellishments vaguely reminiscent of a circus ringmaster or stage magician, most significantly a voluminous cape hanging like a curtain off a metal ring floating above her shoulders.

Not to be mistaken with her excited state in which she appears older with long hair and horns pointing straight up.

title: winter_daphne
body:
[b][i]Daphne odora[/i][/b] (lit. fragrant daphne) is a species of [[flower]]ing [[bush|shrub]] of the genus [i]Daphne[/i] in the family [i]Thymelaeaceae[/i], native to Asia. Commonly called winter daphne, it is known for its showy, fragrant flowers. It blooms in mid to late winter, as the common name suggests.

Winter daphne flowers grow in clusters, usually at the end of stems surrounded by leaves. The flowers have four pointed petals, with two upper petals overlapping the two lower petals; the petals are actually tepals (undifferentiated petals and sepals). The flowers are creamy white and pink to purple, usually whitish or pinkish on the inside and pink to purple on the outside. Although rare, the plant sometimes produces berries after flowering. All parts of the plant are poisonous, especially the berries.

title: ki-adi-mundi
body: Ki-Adi-Mundi is a character from [[Star Wars]], he was a Cerean [[Jedi]] Master and a leading member of the Jedi High Council during the last years of the Galactic Republic. By the time of the Clone Wars, Mundi became a Jedi General of the Grand Army of the Republic. Like his Jedi colleagues, he led the Republic clone troopers against the Separatist Alliance forces in several battles across the galaxy, including the first and second Battles of [[Geonosis]] and the Outer Rim Sieges. During the final year of the Clone Wars, Mundi oversaw the Republic invasion of Mygeeto with the Galactic Marines under his command. During the campaign, Supreme Chancellor [[palpatine|Sheev Palpatine]] instructed the Grand Army soldiers to execute their Jedi leaders per Order 66, an act that resulted in the death of Mundi along with the majority of the Jedi Order.

title: barriss_offee
body:
Character from [[Star Wars]], Barriss Offee is a Mirialan [[Jedi]] apprentice of Luminara Unduli and a close friend of [[Ahsoka Tano]]. She later betrays Ahsoka and frames her for a terrorist bombing after she becomes disillusioned with the Jedi Order's wartime policies. Offee is eventually unmasked and defeated by [[Anakin Skywalker]], resulting in her arrest.

The character has been portrayed by Nalini Krishan in Episode II, and voiced by Meredith Salenger in [[star wars: the clone wars|The Clone Wars]] and Tales of the Empire.

title: zabrak
body:
An alien race in the [[Star Wars]] universe, Zabraks were a near-human carnivorous species native to the planets Iridonia and Dathomir. Most members of the species had distinctive horns atop their heads, as well as two hearts. Although most Zabraks lived on Iridonia, some settled on the planet Dathomir, where the females of the species, known as Nightsisters, ruled over the Nightbrother males and practiced powerful dark side magick. Notably, female Dathomirian Zabraks had paler skin and lacked the cranial horns shared by the rest of the species.

Zabraks fought against the Galactic Empire's attempts to undermine and subvert them, and instead of surrendering, many joined the Alliance to Restore the Republic. Zabraks were considered to be proud, self-determined, and even arrogant to some, and they were one of the most independent species in the galaxy.

title: venator-class_star_destroyer
body:
A [[Star Wars]] spaceship.
The Venator-class Star Destroyer, also known as the Venator-class cruiser, was a class of more than 1,000 meter-long attack cruiser of the Star Destroyer design family that was operated by the navy of the Galactic Republic. Designed by Lira Wessex to feature a double-wedge design and perform a wide range of missions, the Venator was the first class of Star Destroyer to be manufactured by Kuat Drive Yards. Alternatively known as the Republic cruiser, Republic attack cruiser, or Republic Star Destroyer, it was a versatile capital ship capable of serving as both a combatant in ship-to-ship naval warfare and a starfighter carrier, while also being employed as a troop transport, cargo ship, and supply and replenishment vessel. As a warship, Venators were protected by powerful deflector shields and boasted a range of weaponry. For its carrier role, a large flight deck, along with hangars to accommodate a complement of starfighters, gunships, shuttles, armored vehicles and other craft, was contained in the forward section, while three more docking bays were located around the ship. At least two variants existed, the Venator I-class and the Venator II-class.

As the backbone of the Galactic Republic's navies during the Clone Wars, the Venator was commonly employed by the Jedi Generals of the Grand Army of the Republic as their flagships, thus earning the moniker of Jedi cruiser. Deployed across the galaxy against the Confederacy of Independent Systems, Venators saw action in many major engagements, such as the Battle of Christophsis, the Malevolence Campaign, the Battle of Ryloth, and the Second Battle of Geonosis. In the climactic Battle of Coruscant in the waning days of the war, over 1,000 Venators defended the galactic capital Coruscant against a massive Separatist fleet. Eventually, these starships emerged on the victors' side as icons of the conflict.

When the Republic ended with Darth Sidious's purge of the [[Jedi]] Order and his establishment of its successor, the Galactic Empire, the Venator-class Star Destroyers were absorbed into the nascent Imperial Navy. During the early Imperial Era, Venators were utilized to consolidate Imperial authority, and later they fought against Separatist holdouts and fledgling rebel cells. They were also assigned to the private fleets of Moffs, and to flight schools. Others were scrapped on planets like Bracca, where they were dismantled and salvaged by the Scrapper Guild. Although Venators were still active at the time of the Galactic Civil War, they had mostly been replaced by the Imperial-class Star Destroyer, a larger warship modeled on its Republic predecessor.

title: star_wars:_return_of_the_jedi
body:
[b]Return of The Jedi[/b] is the third installment in the original [[Star Wars]] film trilogy, the third film to be produced, and the sixth chronological order. The film was released in theaters on May 25, 1983. It grossed $374 million worldwide during its initial theatrical run, becoming the highest-grossing film of 1983. 

The film stars [[Mark Hamill]], [[Harrison Ford]], [[Carrie Fisher]], Billy Dee Williams, Anthony Daniels, David Prowse, Kenny Baker, Peter Mayhew and Frank Oz.

[[Luke Skywalker]] and friends travel to [[Tatooine]] to rescue their companion [[Han Solo]] from the vile [[Jabba the Hutt]]. The Empire prepares to crush the Rebellion with a more powerful [[Death Star]], while the Rebel fleet mounts a massive attack on the space station. Luke confronts his father, [[Darth Vader]], in a final climactic duel before the evil [[palpatine|Emperor]].

16 years after the release of Return of the Jedi, [[George Lucas]] wrote and directed the prequel trilogy, consisting of the films [[Star Wars: The Phantom Menace|The Phantom Menace]], [[Star Wars: Attack of the Clones|Attack of the Clones]] and [[Star Wars: Revenge of the Sith|Revenge of the Sith]].

title: gun_gun_cut
body:
The scene cut during an [[Ultra Series|Ultra]]'s [[transformation|trans]][[henshin|formation]] which generally depicts them as rapidly growing larger with their [[outstretched arm|arm outstretched]]. Why this specific cut is known as a "gun gun cut" is not known, but the term has been used officially. Otherwise referred to as the 'Ultraman Rise' or 'Ultraman Rising' pose.

While most poses during the cut generally only have one arm outstretched, depending on the cut parodied, both arms can be outstretched, the hand can be in a number of poses (most commonly as a fist), and some later Ultras even have non-static poses during cuts. A select handful of Ultras do not raise their arms when transforming, whether in specific contexts or generally, such as [[Ultraseven]] using the [[Ultra Eye]].

The most commonly parodied version of the cut is [[Ultraman]]'s, with only one arm outstretched and his hand thrust into a fist.

h4. Examples

* !post #513120: From [i]Daikessen! Chou Ultra Hachi Kyoudai[/i]

h4. External links

title: seiken_gakuin_no_maken_tsukai
body:
A light novel series written by "Yuu Shimizu":[https://twitter.com/shimizuMFJ] and illustrated by [[Toosaka Asagi]]. A manga adaptation illustrated by [[Keigen Hichou]] has been serialized in Kadokawa Shoten's shōnen manga magazine Monthly Shōnen Ace since November 2019 and an anime television series adaptation produced by Passione studio aired from October to December 2023. A RPG game was announced in April 2023.

English Title: [i]The Demon Sword Master of Excalibur Academy[/i]

h4. Synopsis

A thousand years ago, the Undead King, [[Leonis Death Magnus]], sealed his own body with a powerful barrier and cast a resurrection spell on himself. He shall rise again in one thousand years to conquer humanity for that is the mission given to him by the Goddess of Rebellion.

In the present time, a young girl named [[Riselia Ray Crystalia]] stumbled upon the ancient ruins of Leonis's mausoleum. Accidentally undoing the seal, Leonis awakens after his thousand-year slumber in the body of a ten-year-old human child. Mistaken to be a refugee of the Voids, Riselia takes Leonis into her care and Leonis begins his mission to uncover what has happened to the world while he slept.

title: sword_art_online
body:
A 2009-current light novel series written by "Kawahara Reki":[https://twitter.com/kunori] and illustrated by [[Bunbun]]. It has multiple manga adaptations, multiple videogames, a three season anime, and three movies.

The series takes place in the near future and focuses on protagonist [[Kirito]] and [[Asuna (sao)|]] as they play through various virtual reality MMORPG worlds.

Initially written in 2002 for the ASCII Media Works’ Dengeki Game Novel Prize (now Dengeki Novel Prize), the author refrained from sending it in due to exceeding the page limit.  Kawahara Reki published it as a web novel and later added 3 more volumes and short stories to the series.  After winning the Dengeki Novel Prize Grand Prize in 2008 for [[Accel World]], ASCII Media Works requested that aside from Accel World if they could also publish Sword Art Online as well. The author agreed and withdrew the web novel version. The series was republished in light novel format in 2009.

The series received an anime adaptation in 2012, which later became highly successful. And went on popularize a whole subgenre of Japanese media known as [[isekai]], which involves having the main character(s) originated from modern world being reincarnated into other worlds.

A movie, [[Sword Art Online the Movie: Ordinal Scale]], was released on February 18, 2017. The movie features a new original story that takes place some time after the second season of the anime.

A second movie, [[Sword Art Online Progressive]], was release on October 30, 2021. The movie retold the original story from the first two episodes of Aincrad Arc but through the perspective of [[Asuna (SAO)|]].

h4. Story arcs

* Aincrad (First Arc, SAO)
* Fairy Dance (Second Arc, ALO)
* Phantom Bullet (Third Arc, GGO)
* Caliburn / Mother's Rosario (Side Story Arcs, ALO)
* Ordinal Scale (OS)
* Alicization (Fourth Arc, Project Alicization)
* Unital Ring (Fifth Arc, UR)

title: twitch_plays_pokemon
body:
An event where tens of thousands of [[Twitch.tv|Twitch]] viewers played a single game of [[Pokemon]] through Twitch's chat system. [[Pokemon RGBY|Pokemon Red]] was conquered on March 1st, 2014 after ~390 hours. This was followed by Pokemon Crystal, Emerald, and (randomized) FireRed.

h4. [[Red (pokemon)|RED]]'s Pokémon

h6. Core Team

* [[Pidgeot]] (aaabaaajss, "Bird Jesus"/"ABBA Jesus")
* [[Omastar]] ("Lord Helix")
* [[Zapdos]] (AA–j, “Archangel of Justice”/"Anarchy Jesus")
* [[Nidoking]] (AAAAAAAAAA, "King Fonz")
* [[Lapras]] (AIIIIIIRRR, "Fresh Prince"/"Air Jordan")
* [[Venomoth]] (AATTVVV, "All Terrain Venomoth"/"Dragon Slayer")

title: warden_(minecraft)
body:
A [[monster|hostile]]/boss mob in [[Minecraft]], introduced since the 1.19 update. A horned, dark teal [[monster]] with wide open mouth, and visible soul particles on its chest that glows cyan. 

It can be summoned by an activated naturally-spawned [[sculk (minecraft)|]] shrieker located in the [[deep dark (minecraft)|]] biome. It is the only blind mob in the game, but still can detect players and other nearby entities through sound vibrations and scent. Wardens can walk as fast as player's sprinting speed. Its massive pool of hitpoints (500, equivalent to 250 hearts)— bolstered by its high-damage melee, ranged sonic attacks that can penetrate walls, immunity to fire and lava, and surprising intelligence —make it one of the most feared mobs in the game. Fighting one is guaranteed to result in the player's character dying.

h4. See also
* [[List of Minecraft characters]]

h4. External links
* "Minecraft Wiki: Warden":https://minecraft.wiki/w/Warden

title: aku_no_musume_(series)
body:
Major arc of [[Evillious Nendaiki]], named after the [[Aku no Musume (vocaloid)|eponymous song]] which spawned the series as a whole. Tells the story of [[Riliane Lucifen d'Autriche]]'s disastrous reign as princess and the aftermath. Also known as "Aku no Monogatari".

The story was adapted into 4 novels, [i]Aku no Musume: Ki no Cloture[/i], [i]Aku no Musume: Midori no Wiegenlied[/i], [i]Aku no Musume: Aka no Praeludium[/i], and [i]Aku no Musume: Ao no Praefacio[/i].

title: shinora
body:
Early predecessor style to [[Decora]], derived from fans of the 1990s idol Shinohara Tomoe. Sometimes informally called "FRUiTS style" due to being commonly displayed in the magazine.

Still colorful, but often uses very clashing colors and patterns such as [[plaid clothes|plaid]], along with [[layered clothes|layering clothes]] and [[scarf|scarves]] instead of accessories like hair ornaments. [[Animal hat]]s, chunky [[buttons]], [[pom pom (clothes)|]]s and [[stuffed toy]]s were especially popular.

title: dragon_ball:_the_breakers
body:
[B]Dragon Ball: The Breakers[/b] is an asymmetrical survival game in the style of [[Dead By Daylight]] that was released on October 14th, 2022. In the game, the player can either control an ordinary human in a team of 7 or one of the many [[Dragon Ball]] villains hunting down these humans. The [[survivor (dbtb)|ordinary humans]] are granted the ability to fight back against the villains using items called "transpheres" that allow them to take the power and form of countless characters in the series.

The game has been confirmed to take place in the same universe as [[Dragon Ball Xenoverse]] and frequently has crossover promotions with the game.

body:
The personification of the Gnevny-class/Anshan-class destroyer [i]An Shan[/i] (pennant number 101) in [[Azur Lane]].

Has dragon horns and green hair, a reference to her theme motif as the Azure Dragon/Seiryuu (a symbol of Imperial China, given that her class was the first destroyer class of China).

Her real-life destroyer counterpart was originally built for Soviet Pacific Fleet use before being transferred to China in 1953 and still exists as a museum ship in Qingdao since 1992.

Voiced by [[Asumi Kana]].

title: forbin_(azur_lane)
body:
[[Azur Lane]]'s personification of the French destroyer [i]Forbin[/i], one of the 14 [i]L'Adroit[/i]-class destroyers. 
Character design by [[Yano Mitsuki (nanairo)|]], voiced by [[Hasegawa Akiko]].

In-game, she is portrayed with [[long hair|long]] [[blonde hair]] and [[green eyes]], with a [[medium breasts|sizable chest size]].
Her outfit consists of a [[white dress]] with a [[cleavage cutout]], sleeveless [[blue jacket]] tied to the center, white [[thighhighs]], [[armored boots]] akin to a knight's, [[white gloves|white]] [[elbow gloves]], and white [[hair ribbon|hair ribbons]].

Her [[rigging]] consists of a single 130 mm gun mount to her right and 550 mm triple [[torpedo tubes]] to her left, held together by her bridge and funnel to her back with a range [[clock]] and [[mast]] that flies a variant of the [[French flag|French tricolor]].

h4. History
In real life, she was part of a squadron in Alexandria that was disarmed by the [[Royal Navy]] under Admiral [[Andrew Cunningham]] after he learned of the disastrous attempt to seize a larger French fleet at Mers-el-Kebir, Algeria.
She was handed over to the Free French in December 1943 with the rest of the Alexandria squadron and served until 1952.

A [[hairband]] made of metal, with a simple design and which may be embellished with gems or other ornaments. Often worn by fantasy heroines, princesses or pop idols.

Compared to a [[crown]], the band of a tiara is usually narrow and shaped like a semi-circle. A tiara is normally worn on the top of the head, not over the forehead like a [[circlet]].

title: emden_(azur_lane)
body:
[[Azur Lane]]'s personification(s) of the Imperial German Navy light cruiser SMS [i]Emden[/i]. Or more specifically the 1908 [i]Dresden[/i]-class light cruiser and the 1916 [i]Koenigsburg[/i]-class light cruiser.

h4. Appearance
Emden appears as [[2girls|two girls]] with one having a light-color scheme and the other with dark colors, each with a [[flower over eye|flower]] over one eye. This is a reference to the two ships named [i]Emden[/i] built by the German Empire, with the latter being a [i]Koenigsburg[/i]-class cruiser, being first laid down in 1916 and inherited the name of the more famous predecessor which were scuttled in 1914.

h4. History
In real life, the first SMS [i]Emden[/i] was the second member of the [i]Dresden[/i]-class light cruisers, powered by older triple expansion engines (think of the engines on the [i]Titanic[/i]) instead of newer steam turbines, the last German warship to be so equipped.

She saw action with the East Asia squadron based in Qingdao and engaged in commerce raiding and an engagement against an Allied fleet in Penang, Malaysia in October 1914. Two months later, she was run aground after sustaining severe damage in an engagement with an Australian cruiser, and her crew were forced to scuttle the ship.

The second SMS [i]Emden[/i] was a [i]Koenigsburg[/i]-class cruiser laid down in 1916. She saw little action for the rest of the war. She is one of the several ships that were scuttled during the internment at Scapa Flow in 1919, though she was beached to save her from sinking by the British. [i]Emden[/i]'s hulk was later transferred to France as reparations before being scrapped in 1926.

title: gwen_tennyson
body:
Cousin of the [[ben tennyson|titular hero]] in [i][[Ben 10]][/i] and its sequels. Casually known as [b]Gwen[/b]. 

In the original series, she has [[short hair|short]] [[orange hair]] and [[green eyes]], and wears a [[hairclip]] and a shirt with [[raglan sleeves]]. In [i][[Ben 10: Alien Force]][/i], she has [[long hair]] instead and wears a [[sweater]] with a [[skirt]]. In the post-timeskip sequels, she becomes [[kevin levin|Kevin]]'s girlfriend.

Due to the broader cultural impact of the original series over its sequels, depictions of Gwen generally skew towards her 10 year old self or make reference to it, over her 15+ year old self (or even 30+ year old self from the original's future episodes).

title: tiger_lily
body:
[b][i]Lilium lancifolium[/i][/b], commonly called tiger lily, is a species of [[lily (flower)|]], family [i]Liliaceae[/i].

Like other lilies, tiger lily flowers are six-petaled and borne on an upright stem. The flowers tend to nod, with six petals bent backwards and six long stamens spread out. The showy flowers are bright [[orange flower|orange]] with black or brown-red spots. There are also yellow and spotless varieties. The leaves are lanceolate (lance-shaped).

Its Japanese name is オニユリ ([b]鬼百合[/b] [i]oni-yuri[/i], lit. [[Oni]] lily). The curved back petals are associated with oni horns, and the bright orange color is associated with red oni.

Not to be confused with [[gloriosa (flower)|]], which has similar features, but unlike tiger lily, gloriosa petals are wavy and spotless.

title: pl-10
body:
The PL-10 (霹雳-10; lit. [i]Thunderbolt[/i]) is a short-range air-to-air [[missile]] developed by the [[China|People's Republic of China]]. Development of the missile commenced in 2004 for use on stealth fighters such as the [[Chengdu j-20]] and it entered production in 2013. According to the assessment by Royal United Services Institute, the PL-10 provides comparable performance to European [[ASRAAM]] and [[IRIS-T]] missiles, while offering superior kinematic performances against [[AIM-9 Sidewinder|AIM-9X]].

body:
[[Azur Lane]]'s personification of the light cruiser USS [i]Marblehead[/i] (CL-12). Character designed by [[Silveroid]]. 

She is a [[dark-skinned female|dark-skinned]] [[gyaru]] with [[blonde hair|blonde]] [[short hair with long locks]] [[pink hair|with a pink]] [[gradient hair|gradient]], [[blue eyes]], and [[large breasts]]. 

Her default outfit comprises a [[white jacket]] with [[sleeves past fingers]], [[wrist scrunchie]], white dress top, [[leotard]], [[black shorts]], [[black thighhighs]], and an [[ID card]] showing her pre-gyaru original form. Her [[rigging]] consists of two twin and four single 152 mm gun mounts.

title: amagi_(azur_lane)
body:
The personification of the battlecruiser [i][[amagi_(battlecruiser)|Amagi]][/i] in [[Azur Lane]], introduced as part of the [i]Crimson Echoes[/i] event. Character design by [[Liduke]], voiced by [[Sawashiro Miyuki]].

She is a [[kyuubi]] [[fox girl]] like her younger sister [[Akagi_(azur_lane)|]], with [[long_hair|long]] [[brown hair]] and [[purple eyes]] with red pupils. Her outfit consists of a [[red haori]] over a [[crane print]] dark [[purple kimono]] with [[bodystocking]] underneath, and an [[oil-paper umbrella]] in her hand in addition to her [[rigging]].

A natural strategist, Amagi is much more level-headed than Akagi, always behaving in a professional manner and being respectful towards the [[Commander (azur lane)|]]. However, she suffers from coughing fits, a reference to how her keel snapped during her conversion to a carrier in an earthquake, and is highly conscious of her own frail health, which is manifested in the story as a [[Wisdom Cube (azur lane)|]] with a crack on it.

The historical [i]Amagi[/i] was supposed to be the first in a four-ship class of battlecruisers, developed as part of the Imperial Japanese Navy's Eight-Eight Fleet Program. However, construction was halted as a result of the Washington Naval Treaty, before she and [i]Akagi[/i] underwent conversion into aircraft carriers. [i]Amagi[/i]'s conversion, however, was cut short when her keel snapped during the Great Kanto Earthquake, forcing her to be scrapped like her other two sister ships two years later. 

[[Amagi (cv) (azur lane)|A UR reimagination of her]] is introduced in the 7th anniversary [i]Ode of Everblooming Crimson[/i] event in September 2024. In the event story, Amagi completed her fateful conversion to an [i]Amagi[/i]-class aircraft carrier, restoring her to full health in the process.

title: san_diego_(azur_lane)
body:
[[Azur Lane]] character based on the [i]Atlanta[/i]-class light cruiser [[USS San Diego (CL-53)]], the second ship to carry the name.

She has [[red_hair|red]] [[twintails]] and [[blue eyes]] and [[large breasts]]. One of her quotes is related to American Shengdiyage's Chinese fertiliser [[Jinkela]]. Her personality is exceedingly air-headed and ditzy, often forgetting information that was recently given to her and being more concerned with having fun.

San Diego is notorious among the fanbase for being the most common Super-Rare drop, a reputation similar to Kantai Collection's [[Naka (kancolle)|]]. She has developed a so-called "cult", dedicated to spreading her message of how she is Number One.

However her [[retrofit (azur lane)|]] (the first one given to an SSR/Super Rare ship) has improved her to the point where "Number One" is unironic even outside of Anti-Air (which she always excelled at).

title: scarecrow_(batman)
body: The Scarecrow is a supervillain appearing in American comic books published by [[DC Comics]]. Created by writer Bill Finger and artist Bob Kane, the character first appeared in World's Finest Comics #3 (September 1941). The Scarecrow has become one of the superhero [[batman|Batman's]] most enduring enemies belonging to the collective of adversaries that make up his rogues gallery.

title: cyborg_(dc)
body: Cyborg (Victor "Vic" Stone) is a superhero appearing in American comic books published by [[DC Comics]]. The character was created by writer Marv Wolfman and artist George Pérez, and first appeared in an insert preview in DC Comics Presents #26 (October 1980).Originally known as a member of the [[Teen Titans]], Cyborg was established as a founding member of the [[Justice League]] in DC's 2011 reboot of its comic book titles, replacing [[Martian Manhunter]].

title: blue_beetle
body: Blue Beetle is the name of three superheroes appearing in a number of American comic books published by a variety of companies since 1939. The most recent of the companies to own rights to Blue Beetle is [[DC Comics]], which bought the rights to the character in 1983, using the name for three distinct characters over the years.

Her base Herrscher of Rebirth outfit consists of a [[sleeveless]] [[white dress]] with asymmetrical straps linking it to her [[white choker]], a white [[thigh strap]] on her left, and [[blue flower]]s. 

Unlike other Herrschers who originate from the [[Cocoon of Finality (honkai impact)|]], hers comes from [[Sa (honkai impact)|]] instead. Having gained a new body, her former body has become that of [[seele_(alter_ego)|her Alter Ego]]. She has two familiars/summons: [[Diana_(honkai_impact)|]] and [[Flora_(honkai_impact)|]].

title: spider-gwen
body:
A [[Marvel]] comics character, first debuted in the Spider-Verse comic book storyline in 2014. Her real name is [b]Gwendolyne Maxine "Gwen" Stacy[/b], a variant of [[Gwen Stacy]] from Earth-65 continuity in which Gwen was bitten by a radioactive spider instead of [[Peter Parker]]. Her codename was [b]Spider-Woman[/b], later changed to [b]Ghost-Spider[/b].

Spider-Gwen has appeared in media other than comic books since her debut, including animated shows, animated films and video games. Her popularity led to the creation of another character based on Gwen Stacy, [[Gwenpool]].

title: biwa_lute
body:
The [b]biwa[/b] (琵琶) is a Japanese short-necked fretted [[lute (instrument)|]], often used in narrative storytelling. The biwa is the chosen instrument of Benten, goddess of music, eloquence, poetry, and education in Japanese Shinto.

The main point of differentiation between the biwa and the [[pipa (instrument)|]] (visually) is that the biwa has a bent neck, while the pipa has a straight neck, like an [[acoustic guitar]].

[[Asuna (SAO)|]]'s original Alfheim Online avatar as the Fairy Queen, Titania. She was forced to use this avatar when she was captured by Fairy King [[Oberon (SAO)|]], during the Fairy Dance Arc of [[Sword Art Online]]. In this avatar, she had [[elf]] [[pointy ears]] and [[fairy]] [[wings]]. She wore a white outfit with a [[long skirt|long]] [[white skirt]], a [[crop top]] showing her [[midriff]], and a red ribbon that went around the topmost part of her top that came together to make a bow. She went barefoot, and wore a white strip around her ankles.

Do not be confused with [[Asuna (SAO-ALO)]], her main Alfheim Online avatar used in subsequent arcs.

title: peanut_the_squirrel
body:
Peanut the Squirrel, a social media star with over 500,000 followers on Instagram and TikTok, was a beloved pet rescued by Mark Longo after his mother was hit by a car.

On October 30, 2024, the New York State Department of Environmental Conservation (DEC) seized Peanut and a raccoon named Fred from Longo's home following anonymous complaints about potential rabies risk and illegal wildlife ownership.
During the raid, Peanut allegedly bit an officer, leading to the euthanization of both animals to test for rabies.

title: krusty_the_clown
body:
[b]Krusty the Clown[/b] is one of the many characters of the American animated comedy sitcom [[The Simpsons]].
He is the long-time clown host of [[bart simpson|Bart]] and [[lisa simpson|Lisa Simpson's]] favorite TV show, a variety show consisting of various kid-friendly sketches and often highly violent cartoons, most notably The [[Itchy & Scratchy]] Show. Despite his cheery onscreen persona, Krusty is actually a cynical, burnt-out, addiction-riddled smoker who is made miserable by show business but continues on anyway. He has become one of the most frequently occurring characters outside the main Simpson family and has been the focus of many episodes, some of which also feature [[Sideshow Bob]].

title: santa's_little_helper
body: Santa's Little Helper is a fictional dog in the American animated television series [[The Simpsons]]. He is the pet greyhound of the Simpson family. He was previously voiced by Frank Welker, and is currently voiced by Dan Castellaneta. The dog was introduced in the first episode of the show, the 1989 [[Christmas]] special "Simpsons Roasting on an Open Fire", in which his owner abandons him for finishing last in a greyhound race. [[Homer Simpson]] and his son [[bart simpson|Bart]], who are at the race track in hope of winning some money for Christmas presents, see this and decide to adopt the dog.

body:
A form of [[bowing]] in which the bower waves one hand in front of themselves, extending the other arm off to the side.

The term "to bow and scrape" comes from the gesture often being a deep bow, resulting in one of the bower's feet scraping backwards on the ground behind them for balance. For Danbooru's purposes, the bower's feet do not need to be scraping (or even visible) for this tag to apply.

title: chiyoda_(azur_lane)
body:
Chiyoda is the second ship of the [i]Chitose[/i]-class light aircraft carriers in [i][[Azur Lane]][/i]. 
Character jointly designed by [[Suisai (suisao)|]] and [[Yuui Hutabakirage]]. 


h4. Appearance 

Chiyoda has [[medium_hair|medium length]] [[red_hair|red hair]] with a single [[hair_ribbon|hair ribbon]] on the left side, [[red_eyes|red eyes]] and [[fox_ears|fox ears]] on her head. 

She wears a black and gold [[fox_mask|fox mask]] on her head. She loosely wears a [[White_kimono|white kimono]] with a dark red and gold [[floral_pattern|floral pattern]] on the sleeves, a black [[halterneck]], [[red_skirt|red]] [[pleated_skirt|pleated skirt]], white [[tabi|tabi socks]] and [[geta|geta sandals]]. She has [[claw_rings|brass claw rings]] on her fingers that serve as a means of controlling her [[shikigami|shikigami]].

She along with her sister got a [[chiyoda_(shimmering_surf)_(azur_lane)|summer CG]] upon being introduced into the game. She wears a [[red_bikini|red bikini]] with golden [[high_heels|high heals]], a [[choker|black choker]] and a [[flower|flower]] in her [[hair_flower|hair]]. She also has a [[beachball]] with her.

h4. Personality

Chiyoda has a playful and mischievous personality. She often slips protective charms in the the commanders clothes.

Both she and Chiyoda are good Kagura dancers, they often rehearse with Fuso and Yamashiro.

h4. History

Chiyoda originally built as the second vessel of the Chitose Class seaplane tenders launched on the 19th November 1937. She along with her sister were both converted and reclassified as Light Aircraft Carriers. As a carrier she participated in the Battle of the Philippine Sea and the Battle of Leyte Gulf.

She would finally meet her end during the battle of Cape Engano on the 25th October 1944 where she along with Zuikaku, Zuihou and Chiyoda were used as a sacrificial decoy force to lure the American fleet away from the landing beaches in the Philippines. She was crippled the 4 bombs dropped by US carrier aircraft and was ultimately finished off by surface gunfire from a surface task force consisting of 4 cruisers and 9 destroyers. Chiyoda sank with her entire crew of 1,470 officers and men, there were no survivors.

h4. Trivia
* Both [i]Chitose[/i] and herself (plus [i][[Ryuuhou (Azur Lane)|]][/i]) are classified as [i]Zuihou[/i]-class CVLs in-game (technically [i][[Shouhou (Azur Lane)|]][/i]-class) despite [i]Zuihou[/i] and the [i]Chitose[/i]-class CVLs not having anything in common apart from being conversions of seaplane tenders.
* She is voiced by Hitomi Sekine who also provided the voice for Chitose.

title: dogeza
body:
An element of traditional Japanese etiquette: kneeling directly on the ground and bowing to prostrate oneself until one's head touches the floor in order to show deference to a greatly revered high-class person, as a deep apology, or to express the desire for a favor from said person.

For the pose itself (without the intent of deference or apology), see [[prostration]].

* !post #5631253

title: ojigi_(bowing)
body:
The classic Japanese [[bowing|bow]]. The bower bends at the waist while keeping their back straight and their head perpendicular to their torso, either placing their hands together in front of them or leaving their arms at their sides. The deeper the bow, the more respect is being shown to the recipient.

title: centaur_(azur_lane)
body:
[[Azur Lane]]'s personification of the aircraft carrier HMS [i]Centaur[/i] (R06). Character design by [[Tony Taka]], voiced by [[Uchida Aya]]. 

She has [[long hair|long]] [[blonde hair]] done [[two side up]] and with an [[ahoge]], [[aqua eyes]], [[pointy ears]], and [[medium breasts]].

Her default outfit consists of a [[white dress]] top with [[breast curtains]] and [[no bra]], [[detached sleeves]], blue [[hair flower]]s, [[white skirt]],  [[white panties]], [[asymmetrical legwear]] ([[single thighhigh]] on her right, [[kneehighs|kneehigh]] on her left), a frilled blue [[thigh strap]] on her left leg, and [[high heels|high-heeled]] [[rudder footwear]]. She uses a [[bow (weapon)|]] much like the US carrier girls, patterned off her real-life hull and masts.

She refers to all the other carrier girls as her [i]senpai[/i] (officially translated as "Elders") on account of the fact that she and her sister were, in real life, laid down in 1944 and commissioned in 1953/1954, well after [[World War II]] had ended.

title: carabiniere_(azur_lane)
body:
[[Azur Lane]]'s personification of the Italian Navy Soldati-class destroyer, [i]Carabiniere[/i]. Character design by [[Kaede (Yumesaki Kaede)|]], voiced by [[Tachibana Rika]].

She is portrayed with [[short hair|short]] [[blonde hair]] and [[purple eyes]]. Her default outfit is the historic [i]Arma dei Carabinieri[/i]'s black-colored [[military uniform]] with its distinctive feathered [[bicorne]], [[black cape]], silver [[epaulettes]], and [[white gloves]]. She also wears black [[knee boots]] with [[paravane|paravanes]] attached to them, a [[single thighhigh]] with a [[garter straps|garter strap]], as well as a [[white belt]] with a [[saber (weapon)|]] attached to it. 

Her [[rigging]] consists of a 533 mm triple torpedo mount on her left and a 120 mm twin gun mount on her right, with the monogram "IR" (meaning "Italian Republic") etched on one of the joints below the gun mount. She is also shown wielding a [[musket]] as a sidearm.

h4. Skins

* !post #3655012: Default
* !post #3655020: [[carabiniere (refreshing sundress) (azur lane)|Refreshing Sundress]]

h4. History
In real life, [i]Carabiniere[/i] was the seventh member of the Soldati-class, launched and completed in 1938. She saw service in the battles of Calabria and Cape Matapan, ultimately surviving the armistice and the war. She was among the destroyers retained by the post-war Italian Navy, who refitted her as an anti-submarine destroyer (pennant D551) before being decommissioned in 1965.

h4. [i]Soldati[/i]-class destroyer
* [b]Carabiniere[/b]

h4. External link
* "Wikipedia: Italian destroyer [i]Carabiniere[/i]":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Italian_destroyer_Carabiniere_(1938)]

title: chris_rock
body:
Christopher Julius Rock (born February 7, 1965) is an American stand-up comedian, actor, writer, producer, and film director.
He developed, wrote, produced and narrated the sitcom [[Everybody Hates Chris]] (2005–2009), which was based on his early life. From 1997 to 2000 HBO aired his talk show The Chris Rock Show.
Rock was cast in starring film roles in Lethal Weapon 4 (1998), Dogma (1999), The Longest Yard (2005), the [[madagascar (series)|Madagascar series]] (2005–2012), I Think I Love My Wife (2007), Grown Ups (2010), Death at a Funeral (2010), Top Five (2014), The Week Of (2018), Spiral (2021), Amsterdam (2022), and Rustin (2023).

h4. External links

* "Wikipedia: Chris Rock":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chris_Rock]

h4.See also

* [[Will Smith slapping Chris Rock (meme)]]

title: everybody_hates_chris
body: Everybody Hates Chris is an American semi-autobiographical sitcom created by [[Chris Rock]] and Ali LeRoi that originally aired on UPN from 2005 to 2006, and then on The CW until 2009. The series is based loosely on Rock's personal experiences as a teenager living in Bedford–Stuyvesant, Brooklyn, New York City from 1982 to 1987. However, Rock's real-life adolescence took place from 1978 to 1984, having been born in 1965.

title: jason_momoa
body:
Joseph Jason Namakaeha Momoa (/məˈmoʊə/; born August 1, 1979) is an American actor. He made his acting debut as Jason Ioane on the syndicated action drama series Baywatch: Hawaii (1999–2001), which was followed by portrayals of Ronon Dex on the Syfy science fiction series [[Stargate: Atlantis]] (2005–2009), and [[Khal Drogo]] in the first two seasons of the HBO fantasy drama series [[Game of Thrones]] (2011–2012). He went on to play the lead roles in the Discovery Channel historical drama series Frontier (2016–2018) and the Apple TV+ science fiction series See (2019–2022).

From 2016 to 2023, Momoa portrayed [[aquaman (dc)|Aquaman]] in the [[DC Extended Universe]] (DCEU), primarily in the films [[Justice League]] (2017), [[aquaman (movie)|Aquaman]] (2018), and Aquaman and the Lost Kingdom (2023), with cameo appearances in other media. Momoa has also played Duncan Idaho in the science fiction film [[dune (series)|Dune]] (2021), and has starred in the action film Fast X (2023).

title: felicity_jones
body:
Felicity Rose Hadley Jones (born 17 October 1983) is a British actress, and started her professional acting career as a child, appearing in The Treasure Seekers (1996) at age 12. She went on to play Ethel Hallow for one series of the television series The Worst Witch and its sequel Weirdsister College. On radio, she has played the role of Emma Grundy in the BBC's The Archers. In 2008, she appeared in the Donmar Warehouse production of The Chalk Garden.
Since 2006, Jones has appeared in the films Northanger Abbey (2007), Brideshead Revisited (2008), Chéri (2009), The Tempest (2010), [[The Amazing Spider-Man 2]] (2014), and True Story (2015). Her performance in the 2011 film Like Crazy was met with critical acclaim and awards including a special jury prize at the 2011 Sundance Film Festival. Her performance as Jane Hawking in the 2014 biographical film The Theory of Everything earned her nominations for the BAFTA and Academy Award for Best Actress.

In 2016, Jones starred in the adventure-thriller Inferno, the fantasy drama A Monster Calls, and the space opera [[Rogue One: A Star Wars Story]] as [[Jyn Erso]]. She has since portrayed Ruth Bader Ginsburg in the biopic On the Basis of Sex (2018), and has starred in the streaming films The Aeronauts (2019), The Midnight Sky (2020), and The Last Letter from Your Lover (2021).

title: howto:copyright
body:
[expand=Table of Contents]
* "Overview":[#dtext-definition]
* "Criteria":[#dtext-criteria]
** "Qualifying Criteria":[#dtext-qualifying-criteria]
** "Disqualifying Criteria":[#dtext-disqualifying-criteria]
* "Guidelines":[#dtext-guides]
* "Return":[#dtext-go-back]
[/expand]

h4#definition. What is the "Copyright" tag in Danbooru?

On Danbooru, the term "copyright" means "the anime/game/comic/movie/etc from which a character originates". [b]It does NOT mean "anything that is copyrighted".[/b]

Posts not based on any established works should be tagged with the [[original]] copyright tag.

If you're unsure if something should be a copyright tag, ask yourself, "Are there characters within this?" If the answer is "no", then leave it as a "General" tag.

h4#criteria. Criteria

h6#qualifying_criteria. What types of things SHOULD be a copyright tag?

Any anime/tv show/game/book/comic/movie, or a company that makes these types of things. Examples: [[K-ON!]], [[House M.D.]], [[Embodiment of Scarlet Devil]], [[Harry Potter (series)|]], [[Yotsubato!]], [[Gone with the Wind]], [[Nintendo]], [[Kyoto Animation]].

Even [[doujinshi|self-published works]], fan games, etc. should be copyright typed, for example: [[Touhou Musou Kakyou]] (fan anime), [[Narcissu]] (doujinshi), [[Koumajou Densetsu]], and [[Touhou Mother]] (both are fan games).

Vocaloid songs with at least one image on Danbooru also get copyright tags: for example, [[We are Pop Candy! (Vocaloid)]], [[Rolling Girl (Vocaloid)]].  These should all have the "_(vocaloid)" qualifier on the end to allow them to be grouped easily by a {{*_(vocaloid)}} search, and to avoid ambiguity in the case of ones like [[Knife (Vocaloid)]].

[[tag group:pixiv projects|Pixiv projects]] are also considered copyrights: for example, [[Pixiv Fantasia]], [[Pixiv Festa]].

Musical groups are considered to be copyrights as well: [[Kalafina]], [[Iron Maiden (Band)]].

h6#disqualifying_criteria. What types of things SHOULD NOT be a copyright tag?

There are many types of things that, although they are copyrighted, should not be a copyright tag on Danbooru.

For example, these are simply objects, and so should be general tags.

* Models of cars, car brands: e.g. [[Nissan]], [[Toyota Supra]]
* Food and drink brands: e.g.  [[Caloriemate]], [[Coca-cola Zero]], [[Pocky]].
* Gun types: e.g. [[Barrett M82]], [[P90]]

Tags referring to specific stores or their uniforms should also be general: e.g. [[7-eleven]], [[Anna Miller]].

* However, [[McDonald's]] and [[Pepsi]] are considered a copyright since there are characters such as [[Ronald McDonald]] and [[Pepsiman]] originating from them.

Names of songs from anime should be general: e.g. [[Ren'ai Circulation]], [[Minna no Peace]].

Websites can go either way: [[Wikipedia]] has the character [[Wikipe-tan]] and so it is a copyright, the same with [[Pixiv]], which has [[Chobi (pixiv)|]] and [[Pixiv-tan]]. However, websites with no characters, such as [[Yahoo]] or [[Flickr]] should be general.

h4#guides. How to make a copyright tag.

To make a tag be a copyright tag, prefix it with "copyright:" or "copy:". Remember to replace spaces with underscores (like_this).

Copyright tags should be in the original language, for example [[Umineko no Naku Koro ni]], not [[When the Seagulls Cry]]. If the translated title is widely used, you may "request an alias":/tag_alias_request/new from that to the original language title.

* Note: There are some "grandfathered-in" exceptions to this rule, including [[Spice and Wolf]], [[Neon Genesis Evangelion]], and [[Fullmetal Alchemist]].
* The [[Fatal Frame]] series is also an exception since the original name is the ambiguous word "Zero".
* If there is official romanization of a copyright tag, it will automatically grandfather the tag. Example: [[Azumanga Daioh]] over Azumanga Daiou, [[Yu-Gi-Oh!]] over Yuu-Gi-Ou.
** See forum #168087 for details.
** By default it is partial grandfathering since it is copyright tags which is affected unless there is an attempt to completely grandfather the copyright tag (copyright tags and character tags using English/North American names).
* [[Pokemon]] tags were formerly partly grandfathered-in, as of topic #17160, they are now completely grandfathered-in copyright tags.

If the copyright name includes a subtitle, this may be omitted from the tag name. For example, the tag for "Planetarian ~Chiisana Hoshi no Yume~" is simply [[planetarian]] and "Koihime † Musou ~Doki ☆ Otome Darake no Sangokushi Engi~" becomes [[koihime_musou]]. Similarly, if the original title is the same or similar phrase in two languages, e.g. 銀の匙 Silver Spoon, or 幼なじみは大統領 My girlfriend is the PRESIDENT, you may omit the second part.

Please follow [[howto:romanize|Danbooru's Romanization Guidelines]]. Do not include symbols such as ☆ † ♪ ♥. Do include any punctuation such as ! & + ? . (Please note that the comma, the asterisk, and the percent sign cannot be used in tags.) Replace × with the letter "x".

If you are unsure how to romanize the copyright name, ask in a comment or on the forum.

Do not use a fan-created title to [b]bypass or circumvent two-tag search[/b], such as [[Suzumiya Haruhiko no Yuuutsu]] for {{suzumiya_haruhi_no_yuuutsu genderswap}}.

h4#go_back. Go Back

* "Return to Tags and Sources":/wiki_pages/help:toc.html#dtext-tags_and_sources
* "Return to the Table of Contents":/help/toc
* "Return to the Wiki Help Home Page":/help/home

title: tosaki_mimi_(1st_costume)
body:
The default costume of [[VSPO!]]'s [[Tosaki Mimi]]. This costume comes with two similar versions.

The First Version:
On her head, she wears a [[black hairband|black]] [[rabbit ears|rabbit]] [[fake animal ears|ear]] [[animal ear hairband|hairband]]. Her hair for this costume is styled in the default [[grey hair|grey]] [[long hair]] with [[one side up|one side tied up]] and [[gradient hair|gradient]] into [[pink hair|pink]] at the tips of her hair, [[swept bangs]] with pink [[streaked hair|streak]] at the middle.
For the outfit, she wears a [[white shirt|white]], [[long sleeves|long sleeved]] [[turtleneck shirt]] with [[cleavage cutout]], [spoilers][s][[small breasts|(not that she has anything to show tho)]][/s] [/spoilers] she also wears a [[black jacket|black jacket]] over the shirt, styled in [[off shoulder]] and [[partially open jacket|partially]] [[partially unzipped|unzipped]]. She's wearing black [[suspenders|suspenders]] connected to her [[blue skirt|blue]], [[pleated skirt|pleated]] [[suspender skirt|skirt]] worn in [[high-waist skirt|high waist]] with [[black belt]]. Visibly, the shirt is [[shirt tucked in|tucked into]] the skirt.
Below, she wears [[mismatched thighhighs]], which in her right leg, she wears a [[white thighhighs|white]] [[single fishnet legwear|single]] [[fishnet thighhighs]], while in her left leg she wears a [[black thighhighs|black]] [[torn thighhighs|torn]] [[single thighhigh]]. For shoes, she wears a [[black footwear|black]] [[platform footwear|platform shoes]] resembling [[mary janes]].

The Second Version:
In this version, she switches into a [[short sleeves|short sleeved]] version of the [[white shirt|white]] [[turtleneck shirt]], wearing [[black coat]] over it, a black [[corset]] and [[blue skirt|blue]] [[frilled skirt]]. The [[suspenders]] also stay. She also wears a [[pink collar|pink]] [[belt collar]]. Below the single fishnet thighhigh stays for her right leg, but on the left leg she only wears a black [[thigh strap]] and a [[single sock|single]] [[black socks|black]] [[kneehighs|knee-high]], some visible [[bandaid on leg|bandaids]] on both legs (on thigh on the right leg and below knee on the left leg), and her shoes are ornamented with [[blue bow|blue]] [[footwear bow|bows]].

title: yukio_(marvel)
body:
Yukio (雪緒) is a superhero appearing in American comic books published by [[marvel|Marvel Comics]]. She is a female ninja of Japanese origin and a supporting character of the [[X-Men]], particularly associated with [[wolverine (x-men)|Wolverine]].

Yukio appears in [[The Wolverine]] (2013), portrayed by Rila Fukushima. This version is a mutant with the ability to foresee others' deaths and was adopted by the Yashida family as a child to serve as a companion to Mariko Yashida. In the present, Yukio assists Logan in rescuing Mariko from Viper and Ichirō Yashida.

Yukio appears in [[Deadpool 2]], portrayed by Shioli Kutsuna. This version is a member of the X-Men and the girlfriend of teammate [[Negasonic Teenage Warhead]] with technical prowess and electrokinesis. Due to the latter power, fans suggested that the screenwriters had given Yukio's name to a different character, Surge, but the screenwriters denied this, insisting that Yukio remained the same character.

title: perfect_zeong
body:
A fictional manned giant robot from the [[Gundam]] [[mecha]]verse. It is a [[Mobile Suit]] in the [[Gundam MSV]] series.

The [[Zeong]] in the original [[Mobile Suit Gundam]] was an incomplete prototype; [[Char Aznable]] took to a [[space]] battle despite lacking its legs.

The [b]Perfect Zeong[/b] is what the Zeong would have been with extra armament and a pair of legs to aid balance and kick puny enemy mobile suits around with.
other_names: パーフェクト・ジオング

The 8th [[official alternate costume|costume]] of [[Production Kawaii]]'s [[Amano Nene (Vtuber)|]], as seen in post #7605223. Costume design by [[Yayoi Maka]], live2d model by [[Nokoyama]].

It's a [[sleepwear]]-themed outfit consisting of a [[Cloudtomo (amano nene)|]] [[sleep mask|sleep]] [[character mask]], a [[pink nightgown|pink]] or [[aqua nightgown|aqua]] [[see-through nightgown|see-through]]  [[frilled nightgown]] with matching [[bloomers]], a [[white jacket]] with [[long sleeves|long]] [[gloved sleeves]] [[white thighhighs|white]] [[see-through thighhighs|see-through]] [[lace-trimmed thighhighs]] with [[white garter straps]] and [[blue footwear]] [[sandals]] with Cloudtomos on them.

Her [[official alternate hairstyle]] with this outfit is [[long hair|long]] [[messy hair]] with optional [[hair rings]].

title: lobo_(dc)
body: Lobo (Iberian for "wolf") is a fictional character appearing in comic books published by [[DC Comics]]. He was created by Roger Slifer and Keith Giffen, and first appeared in Omega Men #3 (June 1983). He is an [[alien]] from the utopian planet of Czarnia, and works as an interstellar mercenary and bounty hunter.

title: sinestro
body: Thaal Sinestro (/sɪˈnɛstroʊ/) (or simply Sinestro) is a supervillain appearing in American comic books published by [[DC Comics]], particularly those featuring [[Green Lantern]]. Created by John Broome and Gil Kane, Sinestro is a former Green Lantern Corps member who was dishonorably discharged for abusing his power. He has since endured as the archenemy of the superhero Green Lantern and is the founder of the Sinestro Corps.

title: the_question
body: The Question is a name used by several fictional characters appearing in American comic books published by [[DC Comics]]. Created by Steve Ditko, the Question first appeared in Charlton Comics' [[Blue Beetle]] #1 (June 1967), and was acquired by DC Comics in the early 1980s and incorporated into the DC Universe.

title: sonic_generations
body:
[b]Sonic Generations[/b] (ソニック ジェネレーションズ [i]Sonikku Jenerēshonzu[/i]) is a 2011 platformer video game developed by [[Sonic Team]] and published by [[Sega]] for the Xbox 360, PlayStation 3, PC, and Nintendo 3DS.

Produced in commemoration of the 20th anniversary of the Sonic the Hedgehog series, the game follows [[Sonic the Hedgehog|Sonic]] and [[Tails (Sonic)|]] as they form an alliance with their past selves to stop an evil entity from erasing all time. It features two gameplay styles: "Classic", which plays from a side-scrolling perspective like that of the original [[Sega Mega Drive]] [[Sonic the Hedgehog (classic)|Sonic games]], and "Modern", 3D levels similar to those in [[Sonic Unleashed]] and [[Sonic Colors]].

The Japanese version has different subtitles, [b]White Time and Space[/b] (白の時空 [i]Shiro no Jikū[/i]) for the home consoles, and [b]Blue Adventures[/b] (青の冒険 [i]Ao no Bōken[/i]) for the 3DS version.

A remastered version, [[Sonic x Shadow Generations]], was released in 2024.

h4. External links
* "Sonic Retro: Sonic Generations":https://info.sonicretro.org/Sonic_Generations
* "Wikipedia: Sonic Generations":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sonic_Generations
other_names: ソニックジェネレーションズ

title: sonic_x_shadow_generations
body: A remaster and companion game release of the console/PC version of [[Sonic Generations]] developed by Sonic Team, featuring additional new content with [[Shadow the Hedgehog]] as a playable character. The re-release version contains a new campaign called "Shadow Generations", centering on Shadow as he must stop [[Black Doom]] from taking over the world, as well as new features to Sonic Generations.

title: lazytown
body:
[b]Latibær[/b] (EN: [b]LazyTown[/b]) is a children's educational musical comedy TV series from Iceland. It aired from 2004 to 2014.

The series focuses on eight-year-old Stephanie (Julianna Rose Mauriello in seasons 1-2, Chloe Lang in seasons 3-4) who has just moved to LazyTown. With the help of a “slightly above average” superhero named [[Sportacus]] (Magnus Scheving), she helps the residents of the town live more active lifestyles.

The show became a meme in 2016 with the song We Are Number One, sang by the villain [[Robbie Rotten]] (Stefán Karl Stefánsson), who at the time had cancer.

h4.External links

* "Wikipedia article":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/LazyTown]

title: war_thunder
body:
[b][i]War Thunder[/i][/b] is an online multiplayer combat simulation [[video game]] by Gaijin Entertainment. It's available for Microsoft Windows, Mac OS X, PlayStation 4, and XBox One.

War Thunder features an aerial, ground, and naval combat, with more realistic gameplay compared to Wargaming's similar "World of" series and an option for cross-usage of aerial vehicles in certain mode as close air support.

title: partido_verde_ecologista_de_mexico
body: The Ecologist Green Party of Mexico (Spanish: Partido Verde Ecologista de México, pronounced [paɾˈtiðo ˈβeɾðe ekoloˈxista ðe ˈmexiko], PVEM or PVE) is a green political party in [[Mexico]]. Founded in 1986, the party is associated with Jorge González Torres and his son Jorge Emilio González Martínez. It has seldom gotten more than 10% of the vote nationwide, but in the 21st century has joined alliances with different major parties (PAN in the federal elections of 2000, PRI from 2003 to 2018, and most recently MORENA from 2019 on).

title: hachimaki
body:
A type of Japanese [[headband]] made of cloth or twine worn to signify dedication to extreme effort. 
A plane hachimaki is commonly used in a sports day / festival of Japanese school to indicate the team color and to try to increase their motivations / kiai (気合, "fighting spirit").
Another common type of hachimaki is printed a red circle of Japanese flag or previously rising sun emblem or / and a short inspirational slogan meant to be displayed across the forehead.

If the headband is twisted, that is called a [[nejiri hachimaki]] which is commonly worn by participants of a Japanese festival.

h4. Examples
* !post #7846176: Red and white hachimakis are worn  in the sports day at school.
* !post #5612240: A red hachimaki with a [[gakuran]].
* !post #7552466: Wearing a white hachimaki with a red circle and a short slogan as a part of an [[ouendan]] uniform.
* !post #7604955: Wearing a hachimaki in order to boost her motivation.
* !post #7585504: Wearing a hachimaki with a message to the [[idol]] her cheering.
* !post #7937430: [[nejiri hachimaki]]  [tn]| A traditional hachimaki worn during festivals (often with a [[mizu happi]]).[/tn]

h4. See Also

* [[nejiri hachimaki]]
* [[bousouzoku]]
* [[ouendan]]

title: the_haunted_mansion
body:
A long-running attraction in [[disneyland|Walt Disney Theme Parks]]. The mansion, as its title implies, is inhabited by ghosts, and  the audience does a tour of the house. Its best known feature is the Stretching Room, a small room in the mansion with four large portraits that "stretches"  to reveal the more macabre halves of the portraits hanging above the audience; and the Ballroom, with illusions of dozens of ghosts waltzing.

A movie based on the attraction was released in 2003. Another one released in 2023, unrelated to the 2003 movie. Its Hong Kong Disneyland equivalent is the Mystic Manor.

title: avrora_(azur_lane)
body:
[[Azur Lane]] character. The personification of the Russian cruiser [i]Aurora[/i].

Not to be confused with [[Aurora (Azur Lane)|]], a Royal Navy ship with a similar name.

Historically one of the participants of the battle of Tsushima and October Revolution, ultimately becoming one of the last two preserved survivors of the battle in the present-day alongside [[Mikasa (Azur Lane)|]]. 
In-game, she was the first [[Northern Parliament (emblem)|]]/Russian faction ship implemented (as reward for closed beta testers). Reappeared in a mini-event in August 2019 before being made permanently available with the [i]Northern Overture[/i] event in early 2020.

title: rex_(xenoblade)
body:
Protagonist of [[Xenoblade Chronicles 2]].

An optimistic boy whose job is a salvager where he performs rescue and retrieve missions. 

Becomes the Driver of [[Pyra (xenoblade)|]]/[[Mythra (xenoblade)|]].

He reappears in [i][[Xenoblade Chronicles 3: Future Redeemed]][/i], being not only significantly older but outright bigger than his previous appearence as well as missing an eye.
In the context of [i][[Xenoblade Chronicles 3]][/i]'s main game, this hints him as [spoilers]the mentor of Founder [[Linka (Xenoblade)|Cassini]] of the City.[/spoilers]
He also has a cameo [spoilers]in the ending in a photo with him and the rest of the main XC2 cast surrounding Pyra, Mythra and Nia with newborns.[/spoilers]

title: laharl
body:
Evil Tyrant Overlord from [[Disgaea]].

After waking up from a two-year "nap", Laharl rules over his father, King Krichevskoy's, kingdom with an iron fist!

He's stubborn, power-hungry, arrogant, a natural-born brawler, and had a weakness for humongous boobs. By weakness, I mean he gets sick by the sight of them. (Etna and Flonne are flat, so they don't bother him in that area.)

Along with Flonne and Etna, Laharl is a recurring character throughout the Disgaea Universe. He and the girls have also appeared in other games made by Nippon Ichi, such as Phantom Brave and Makai Kingdom and The Guided Fate Paradox.

title: grogu
body:
A fictional [[alien]] character from the [[Star Wars]] universe.

[spoilers]An infant (roughly 50 years old during the events of [[The Mandalorian]]) member of [[Yoda]]'s species, found by [[Din Djarin]] who then starts to watch over him. A former member of the [[Jedi]] Order, he was saved by another Jedi during [[star_wars:_revenge_of_the_sith|order 66 and the clone trooper attack on the Jedi Temple]].[/spoilers] 

Because his real name wasn't known until chapter 13 of [i]The Mandalorian[/i], other characters mostly referred to him as just [b]the Child[/b] for the first 12 chapters; however, he was arguably better known among viewers by the nickname [b]Baby Yoda[/b].

title: zanzibar_(space_shuttle)
body:
A fictional military [[space shuttle]] from the [[Gundam]] [[mecha]]verse. It first appeared in the [[Mobile Suit Gundam]] anime TV series from 1979.

It is a heavy armed and armored combat space shuttle used by the Principality of [[Zeon]] as a commander cruiser during their invasion of Earth.

title: norris_packard
body:
A fictional antagonist character from the [[Gundam]] [[mecha]]verse. He first appeared in the [[Gundam 08th MS Team]] OVA from 1996. 

[b]Norris Packard[/b] is a very dangerous [[Zeon]] veteran ace pilot. His mobile suit of choice is the [[Gouf Custom]].

title: blex_forer
body:
A fictional character from the [[Gundam]] universe. He first appeared in the [[Zeta Gundam]] anime TV series from 1985.

[b]Blex Forer[/b] is the [[military]] veteran leader of the [[aeug|Anti Earth Union Group]] (or more correctly translated, the Anti United Earth Government Group), who travels aboard the [[Argama]] during its initial tour of duty. 
 
A [[serious]], intelligent and calm looking, [[beard]]ed [[blonde hair]]ed man. Formerly a high-ranking officer in the [[Earth Federation Space Forces]], Blex was outraged by the atrocities of [[titans_(gundam)|the Titans]], and used his political and business connections with [[Anaheim Electronics]] to organize a very well armed, well supplied and well equipped resistance group. 

Well-acquainted with his enemies [[Bask Om]] and [[Jamitov Hymen]], Blex plots his counter-strategies against them with the calm intelligence of a veteran [[chess]] player. [spoilers]However, he is betrayed and shot by a Titans operative during a peace summit in the city of Dakar and dies in the arms of [[Quattro Bajeena]], telling him to become the new leader of the AEUG, but as [[Char Aznable]], the legendary "Red Comet" from [[Zeon]].[/spoilers]
other_names: ブレックス・フォーラ

title: dr._evil
body: Douglas "Dougie" Powers, commonly known as Dr. Evil, is a fictional character portrayed by Mike Myers in the [[Austin Powers]] film series. He is the main antagonist and Austin Powers' nemesis (and secret twin brother). He is a parody of [[James Bond]] villains, primarily Ernst Stavro Blofeld. Dr. Evil routinely hatches schemes to terrorize and take over the world, and is usually accompanied by "Number Two", his second-in-command who fronts his evil corporation Virtucon Industries, his personal assistant Frau Farbissina, and his sidekick Mini-Me, a dwarf clone of himself.

title: chris_griffin
body:
One of the main characters in [[Family Guy]].

He is the middle child of the Griffin family. He is 13 in the first three seasons, 14 in the fourth through nineteenth season, and 15 in the twentieth season. Son of [[Peter Griffin|Peter]] and [[Lois Griffin]].
He is voiced by the American actor, producer, and writer [[Seth Green]] and first appeared on television, along with the rest of the Griffin family, in the episode "Death Has a Shadow" on January 31, 1999.

title: tie_fighter_(video_game)
body: Star Wars: TIE Fighter is a 1994 [[Star Wars]] space flight simulator and space combat video game, a sequel in the Star Wars: X-Wing series. It places the player in the role of an Imperial starfighter pilot during events that occur between [[Star Wars: The Empire Strikes Back|The Empire Strikes Back]] and [[star wars: Return of the Jedi|Return of the Jedi]]

title: dengar
body: Character from [[Star Wars]], Dengar, also known as Dengar the Demolisher, was a Corellian human bounty hunter.

title: ithorian
body: Ithorians, commonly referred to as hammerheads or as leathernecks as an insult, were a sentient species from the planet Ithor in the [[Star Wars]] franchise. Ithorians had two mouths on the opposite sides of their necks, giving them a deep, rumbling voice. Most Ithorians were peaceful and revered nature. The species' pacifism was so strong that they exiled violent individuals from their homeworld of Ithor. Notable Ithorians include Dok-Ondar, a collector on Batuu, and Momaw Nadon, an Ithorian gardener who was exiled from his homeworld.

title: terminator_2:_judgment_day
body:
A 1991 American film directed by James Cameron. The sequel to the 1984 film [[The Terminator]] and the second film in the [[Terminator (series)|]] franchise. title: homer_simpson_backs_into_bushes_(meme)

title: ralph_wiggum
body: Ralph Wiggum is a recurring character in the animated series [[The Simpsons]]. He is voiced by Nancy Cartwright. Ralph is characterized largely by his frequent non-sequiturs which range from nonsensical and bizarre to profound. His dim-witted behavior lends him an air of blissful ignorance.
